# Test environment — copy to `.env.test` and fill in.
#
# `.env.test` is gitignored; never commit a populated copy.
#
# Why this file exists (Phase 8.5): the pytest suite's destructive fixtures
# TRUNCATE `claims`, `audit_log`, and `policy_chunks`. If the suite resolved to
# the deployed Neon database, running `pytest` would wipe production data — which
# is exactly what happened during Phase 8.4. The test fixtures now resolve their
# database from `TEST_DATABASE_URL` (this file) in preference to `DATABASE_URL`,
# and refuse, loudly, to run against any `*.neon.tech` host.
#
# One-time local setup:
#   1. Create the test database (reuses the dev-DB script via DEV_DB_NAME):
#        DEV_DB_NAME=agentic_claims_test ./scripts/setup-dev-db.sh
#   2. Copy this file:
#        cp .env.test.example .env.test
#   3. Set TEST_DATABASE_URL below to your local test DB, substituting your
#      Postgres user. It must NOT be a .neon.tech host.

# Required for running the test suite locally. Local Postgres only — never Neon.
TEST_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER@localhost:5432/agentic_claims_test
